name: Shady Daruma
description: When my grandma took me over to her friend's houses, I would always color in the Daruma's other eye without them knowing.  That's probably why my wishes always came true.

name: Signature J-Tree
description: J on the front left / Big J on the back.

name: Rice Eggs & Spam
description: "The neko in the hat" was one of my favorite books to read when I was a kid.

name: J-Tables
description: This first time I've ever wanted Technics turntables is when I watch the movie "Juice". If you haven't seen it...watch it.

name: Japangeles All-Stars
description: Make sure you rock this shirt with your Chucks!

name: Daruma Vader
description: May the Daruma be with you..

name: Destinations
description: Putting Japangeles on the map.

name: DARUMA LOVE
description: Daruma never falls down.

name: O.G. Nihon/LA
description: Fresh out of the rice cooker!  Original Japangeles trademarked "I Love Nihon in Kanji w/ L.A. outlined".

name: Lucky Neko
description: I highly recommend wearing this shirt at the California Hotel in Las Vegas.  You'll definitely get the obasans rubbing your shirt for good luck!

name: JPNGLS
description: Showing love to Run–D.M.C. a group widely acknowledged as one of the most influential acts in the history of hip hop culture.

name: Chopsticks 101
description: Watching Mr. Miyagi catch the fly with chopsticks on the original Karate Kid inspired me to learn how to use them! Wax on my friends!

name: Neighborhood Watch
description: Be a part of the Little Tokyo neighborhood watch! Keep your eyes open out there! (also available in black and heather grey).

name: Daruma Nation
description: The days when you spent your weekends in East L.A. as a kid...your tough uncle in the family made you watch the Raiders play, and when the commercials came on he made you run to the local liquor store to get him snacks. And I always kept the change.

name: Purple & Yellow
description: Remembering the days of the Great Western Forum during playoffs… the love for LA, purple and yellow, excitement at seeing Magic, Worthy, Rambis, and Van Excel spank the Portland Trailblazers.  Oh, and we can't leave out Chick, Jack Nicholas, and that mysteriously Asian lady that sits next to him.

name: Chavez Ravine
description: Playing in the J baseball league as a pitcher, I always tried to mimic Orel Hershiser's form. Till this day...I still couldn't figure out how Fernando Valenzuela pitched looking up, and how Kurt Gibson hit that game winning home run...injured!  Memories at the Chavez Revine.

name: I Daruma Nihon/LA
description: Wear this shirt and ask people if they see the L.A.?

name: LAX > NRT
description: A must have when you're flying to Japan.  Let everyone know @ LAX where you're flying to.

name: Hadouken!
description: Remember running over to your local liquor store, with a bag of quarters in hand to line up in front of the arcade to play until your fingers blistered? Watch your back, doing the Guile Freeze on a guy bigger than you can get your little ass kicked!

name: Shooting Crane
description: Shoot cranes not bullets.

name: Yo! Jtv Raps
description: Just remembering when Yo! Mtv Raps came on TV, I would always rush into my room to find a blank VHS to record my favorite videos.  Oh the love for 90's rap & hip hop.

name: I Daruma Nihon/Hawaii
description: Hawaii = spam, portuguese sausage, hot girls in bikini, warm island breeze, Zippy’s, Matsumoto shaved ice...One favor, Hawaii, can you please ease up on the ABC stores?

name: I Daruma Nihon/SF
description: SF = Amazing city, amazing food and amazing people!  The homeless guy hiding behind the tree leaves always seems to scare me every time.

name: Daruma Busters
description: Who you gonna call?

name: Candlestick
description: Candlestick park is probably on my top 3 baseball stadiums. One of these days I'm going to rent a canoe and just sit out there waiting for a foul ball.

name: The Big "A"
description: Don't think we need the rally monkey this season with Mr. Albert in the line up! (This shirt comes in American Apparel only)

name: Top Crane
description: I know everyone that watched this had to close their eyes during the 80's love scene by Tom and Kelly!  Those that did...we know you peeked a little through your fingers.

name: Baby Japangeles
description: For the cool babies out there.

name: Shady Daruma or Lucky Neko Keychain
description: Now have Shady Daruma or Lucky Neko in your pockets for luck!

name: J Koozies
description: Japangeles now keeps your drinks cold. Fits cans and bottles.  2 designs on 1 koozie.

name: Dope Things Inside Tote
description: We had it on our shopping bags...now available on canvas totes.
